  "doc_id": "48671",
  "text": "Participants underwent a 2-h 75-gram oral glucose tolerance test. Prediabetes was defined according to American Diabetes Association criteria [CITATION_1] . Insulin resistance was assessed by the homeostasis model assessmentinsulin resistance (HOMA-IR) index. Dyslipidemia was characterized by LDL-cholesterol ≥ 130 mg/dL and/or lipid-lowering agents use. Hypothyroidism was defined by TSH levels > 4.0 IU/L and free T4 < 0.8 µg/dL, while hyperthyroidism by THS levels < 0.4 IU/L and free T4 ≥ 1.9 µg/dL.",
